        </div>
        <div class="faq-block">
            <div class="question-box">
                <div class="ques" onclick="hideAnswer(this)">
                    <p>How to register to the website ?</p>
                    <img src="./static/images/chevron-down-solid.svg">
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>You just need to follow 4 steps to start banking with us. Lets introduce to you with account
                        creation steps.</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Fill your basic details</li>
                        <li>Upload your KYC Details</li>
                        <li>Validate Your Email Account</li>
                        <li>Create Password and Confirm</li>
                        </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="question-box">
                <div class="ques" onclick="hideAnswer(this)">
                    <p>What's the document required for KYC ?</p>
                    <img src="./static/images/chevron-down-solid.svg">
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>You just need two documents: </p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Aadhaar Card</li>
                        <li>Pan Card</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="question-box">
                <div class="ques" onclick="hideAnswer(this)">
                    <p>How to view the tranaction history ?</p>
                    <img src="./static/images/chevron-down-solid.svg">
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p>To view Transaction history follow the steps given below: </p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Open Login page</li>
                        <li>Login to account</li>
                        <li>Click on hamburger menu</li>
                        <li>Click on Transaction history option</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>

